    3724             : /*

    3754             :       if ((cat_prev_ch = pp_lexical_category[prev_ch-CHAR_MIN]) ==    \
    3755             :                                                          PLC_SINGLETON || \

    4594             : 
    4595             : 
    4596             : /*
    4597             : The routines that follow are used to detect idioms used to guard against
    4598             : multiple inclusions of a given file.  If such idiom is found, the
    4599             : front end will completely suppress any subsequent attempts to re-include
    4600             : the file.
    4601             : 
    4602             : The idioms supported are #ifndef guard code, and "#pragma once" directives.
    4603             : Files using #ifndef guards have the form:
    4604             : 
    4605             :         ... Optional comments ...
    4606             :         #ifndef NAME
    4607             :         #define NAME
    4608             :         ... Body of include file ...
    4609             :         #endif
    4610             : 
    4611             : #ifndef and #ifdef forms of this are supported.  In addition these forms
    4612             : are accepted, but only if they do not have any embedded comments:
    4613             :  
    4614             :         #if !defined(NAME)
    4615             :         #if defined(NAME)
    4616             : 
    4617             : This include guard detection mechanism is implemented using a simple
    4618             : state machine.  The state information is recorded in the input stack
    4619             : entry.
    4620             : 
    4621             :             (*)                      (*)
    4622             :       ---------------> FAIL <-------------------
    4623             :       |                STATE                    |
    4624             :       |                  ^                      |
    4625             :       |          level-0 | #else/#elif          |
    4626             :       |                  |                      |
    4627             :       |                  |         #endif       |
    4628             :     START  #ifdef   INTERMEDIATE------------>ACCEPT
    4629             :     STATE---------->   STATE   ---+           STATE
    4630             :       |    #ifndef       | ^      |             |
    4631             :       |                  | | (*)  |             |
    4632             :       |                  | -------|             |
    4633             :       |                  |                      |
    4634             :       |                  |                      |
    4635             :       |          #pragma | once                 |
    4636             :       |                  v                      |
    4637             :       |  #pragma       ONCE      #pragma        |
    4638             :       |--------------> STATE <------------------|
    4639             :           once         ^   |       once
    4640             :                        |   |
    4641             :                        |(*)|
    4642             :                        -----
    4643             : 
    4644             : 
    4645             : 
    4646             : In the above diagram, comments do not count as tokens at all, while
    4647             : (*) refers to any token other than those marking the other transitions.
    4648             : 
    4649             : In the case of the INTERMEDIATE state (which is what the file is in during
    4650             : the body, if an opening #ifndef has been seen), if a matching #else is
    4651             : seen, we know that subsequent inclusions cannot be suppressed.
    4652             : 
    4653             : Once the file has reached the ACCEPT state, if any token is seen, then
    4654             : the file goes into the FAIL state.
    4655             : 
    4656             : Also, once the file gets into the ONCE state, it will never move out.
    4657             : 
    4658             : Most of this determination is done in get_token(), and the
    4659             : routines that handle the #ifdef, #ifndef and #pragma directives (in
    4660             : preproc.c).
    4661             : 
    4662             : The final accept-state check is performed in pop_input_stack().
    4663             : 
    4664             : On subsequent includes, the file history information is checked to
    4665             : determine whether the file contained a multiple inclusion guard.  If
    4666             : so, the include is suppressed.
    4667             : */
    4668             :

   12962    34272300 : a_token_kind get_token(void)
   12963             : /*
   12964             : Scan the next token of input, and return its kind.  The kind of token is
   12965             : also saved in curr_token.
   12966             : 
   12967             : If fetch_pp_tokens is TRUE when this routine is called, a preprocessing
   12968             : token (pp-token) is fetched instead of a regular token.  Constants are
   12969             : not converted (and numeric ones are returned as pp-numbers); adjacent
   12970             : string literals are not concatenated; keywords are not recognized; and
   12971             : errors are not issued for malformed tokens.  Also, start_of_curr_token
   12972             : and end_of_curr_token will be set to point to the beginning and end of
   12973             : the current token, and len_of_curr_token will be set to its length.
   12974             : 
   12975             : If expand_macros is TRUE, preprocessing macros are expanded as they are
   12976             : scanned.  The caller sees only the tokens after expansion.  If a macro name
   12977             : is preceded by an LE_INERT_MACRO or LE_TEMPORARILY_INERT_MACRO escape
   12978             : sequence, the macro is not expanded and the identifier is returned to the
   12979             : caller with curr_token_is_inert_macro set to TRUE; in addition, if the
   12980             : escape sequence is LE_TEMPORARILY_INERT_MACRO,
   12981             : curr_token_is_temporarily_inert_macro is set to TRUE.
   12982             : 
   12983             : When fetch_pp_tokens is FALSE, do_string_literal_concatenation controls
   12984             : whether adjacent string literals are concatenated.
   12985             : 
   12986             : If in_preprocessing_directive is TRUE, the definition of white space is
   12987             : changed to that for within preprocessing directives, and newline is

   15388             : 
   15389        1088 : static void get_destructor_or_finalizer_name(
   15390             :                                     a_type_ptr   field_sel_type,
   15391             :                                     a_boolean    is_file_scope_qualified_name,
   15392             :                                     a_symbol_ptr qualifier_sym,
   15393             :                                     a_boolean    is_expr_context)
   15394             : /*
   15395             : The current token is the "~" at the start of a destructor name, or the "!" at
   15396             : the start of a C++/CLI finalizer name.  Scan the name and build a locator for
   15397             : the destructor or finalizer name in locator_for_curr_id.  is_expr_context is
   15398             : TRUE if this call is for a reference to a destructor or finalizer in an
   15399             : expression context (as opposed to a declarator).
   15400             : 
   15401             : A destructor or finalizer declaration can only use the true name of the class.
   15402             : A destructor or finalizer reference (in a field selection operation), on the
   15403             : other hand, can use either the true name of the class or can use a typedef
   15404             : that refers to the class.  Because of this, the lookup of the name that
   15405             : follows the "~" in a destructor reference or the "!" in a finalizer reference
   15406             : is quite complicated.
   15407             : 
   15408             : If the destructor or finalizer reference is not a qualified name the lookup is
   15409             : done as a normal lookup and a lookup in the class of the right operand of the
   15410             : field selection.
   15411             : 
   15412             : If the reference is a qualified name the lookup is done as a normal lookup,
   15413             : and a lookup in the scope that contains the class specified in the qualifier.
   15414             : For example:
   15415             : 
   15416             :         ::A::~B         B is looked up in the file scope
   15417             :         X::A::~B        B is looked up in X
   15418             : 
   15419             : In addition to these lookups, the name of the destructor or finalizer is
   15420             : compared with the name of the class of the right operand of the field
   15421             : selection.
   15422             : 
   15423             : If any of these lookups result in a class that matches the class of the
   15424             : field selection operation, that result is used as the destructor or finalizer.
   15425             : Otherwise, each of the lookup results is checked to see if it matches
   15426             : a base class of the field selection.  If exactly one of the lookups
   15427             : matches a base class, that result is used.  If more than one matches, the
   15428             : lookup is ambiguous.  If no match is found, the original name is converted
   15429             : to a destructor or finalizer name (e.g., "X" is changed to "~X") and a lookup
   15430             : error will be diagnosed by the caller.
   15431             : 
   15432             : The caller is responsible for ensuring that the current token is "~", or "!"
   15433             : in the C++/CLI finalizer case, before calling this routine.  This routine is
   15434             : called only in C++ mode.
   15435             : 
   15436             : field_sel_type is NULL except when scanning the right operand of a field
   15437             : selection operator, in which case it points to the class type of the left
   15438             : operand.  qualifier_sym points to a symbol that describes the qualifier when
   15439             : the destructor or finalizer is part of a qualified name (e.g., "A::B::~B").
   15440             : */

   19374             : /*
   19375             : Determine whether the current token is the start of a "generalized
   19376             : identifier" -- a qualified name, identifier, operator name, conversion name,
   19377             : destructor name, or C++/CLI finalizer name.  If the token does begin an
   19378             : identifier, the tokens that make up the identifier are coalesced into a single
   19379             : token.  This consists of scanning the tokens that make up the identifier,
   19380             : retaining the information conveyed by the tokens in the symbol locator,
   19381             : setting curr_token to tok_identifier, and setting pos_curr_token to the
   19382             : position of the first token in the sequence.  We return TRUE if an identifier
   19383             : was found, otherwise we return FALSE.
   19384             : 
   19385             : Pointer to members are coalesced into a tok_ptr_to_member. We return
   19386             : FALSE for pointer to members.  Similarly, the C++/CLI X::typeid construct
   19387             : is coalesced into a tok_cli_typeid and FALSE is returned.
   19388             : 
   19389             : Returns TRUE and sets curr_token to tok_identifier for the
   19390             : following cases:
   19391             :         
   19392             :         ::i
   19393             :         X::i
   19394             :         ::X::i
   19395             :         ::A::B::i
   19396             :         A<int>::i
   19397             :         A::operator =
   19398             :         A::operator int
   19399             :         A::~A() 
   19400             :         A:: ... anything except * ...
   19401             :         NS::i
   19402             :         NS::A::i
   19403             :         decltype(expr)::something
   19404             :         i
   19405             :         operator =
   19406             :         operator int
   19407             :         ~A              When options & GID_DTOR_RECOGNIZED = TRUE
   19408             :         !A              When options & GID_DTOR_RECOGNIZED and
   19409             :                           cli_or_cx_enabled are both TRUE
   19410             :         A<int>            Template reference will be coalesced
   19411             :         NS::A<int>        Template reference will be coalesced
   19412             :         int::~int       When options & GID_VACUOUS_DTOR_RECOGNIZED = TRUE
   19413             :         int::!int       When options & GID_VACUOUS_DTOR_RECOGNIZED and
   19414             :                           cli_or_cx_enabled are both TRUE
   19415             :

   19417             :

   19419             :         A<int>::* Template reference will be coalesced

   19422             : constructs:

   19443             :

   19445             : identifiers to be recognized and/or allowed.
